title: Tassel, late 16th–early 17th century
medium:
Medium: linen
Technique: braided and knotted
creditline: Bequest of Richard Cranch Greenleaf in memory of his mother, Adeline Emma Greenleaf
description: Pear-shaped linen tassel, braided and knotted. Short double loops attached to pear-shaped center from which hang five units made of small circular center with extensive knotting surrounding center part.
